<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,1254,1999]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1866,1891]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[322,445,1866,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nielsoni">
<emphasis box="[322,445,1866,1891]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">H. nielsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<typeStatus box="[719,817,1866,1891]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">holotype</typeStatus>
male and 
<typeStatus box="[933,1040,1867,1891]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">paratypes</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1223,1866,1891]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. It is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[419,480,1902,1927]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">India</collectingCountry>
. The population from 
<collectingCountry box="[743,801,1902,1927]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">India</collectingCountry>
has different coloration compared to that found in 
<collectingCountry name="Sri Lanka" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. It resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[395,531,1940,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arcuatus">
<emphasis box="[395,531,1940,1963]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">H. arcuatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has the aedeagal shafts tapered distad of the gonopore with the apical curvature less pronounced with the style more elongate.
</paragraph>
